                        "name": "9.A.7 Intramural expenditure on R&D in relation to GDP",
                      
                        "goal": "Goal 9. Industry, innovation and infrastructure",
                      
                        "priority": "Increased competitiveness of the region by increasing the research and innovation potential (Development of institutional potential for research and development, supporting cooperation between the research sector and the economy)",
                      
                        "definition": "Total internal expenditure incurred in a given year on R&D activities conducted in the reporting unit, regardless of the source of funds, in relation to GDP.",
                      
                        "unit": "percent",
                      
                        "dimensions": "total",
                      
                        "methodology": "Research and Development (R&D) Creative work undertaken in a methodical manner to increase the resources of knowledge - including knowledge of mankind, culture and society - and to create new applications for existing knowledge.R&D includes: 1. scientific research - basic research - applied research (identical to application research) 2. development work.Internal R&D expenditures: Expenditures incurred in the reporting year for R&D work performed in the reporting entity, regardless of the source of the funds. They include both current expenditures and capital expenditures on fixed assets related to R&D activities, but do not include depreciation of fixed assets.",
                      
